1
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:36,920
MAIN TITLE

2
00:03:02,040 --> 00:03:04,120
Don't blame me.
Don't blame me. Don't blame me.

3
00:03:48,200 --> 00:03:51,320
EPISODE TITLE

4
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:57,400
XINYA FASHION, CASUAL WEAR

5
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:10,480
YONG'S FASHION

6
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:22,280
PERSON IN CHARGE: SUN ZHENGYONG

7
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:27,240
Young man, is Mr. Sun around?

8
00:04:27,320 --> 00:04:28,360
I want to pick up some stock.

9
00:04:28,440 --> 00:04:29,360
He's gone out to restock.

10
00:04:29,960 --> 00:04:32,240
- When did he leave?
- No idea.

11
00:04:32,320 --> 00:04:34,440
If you're picking up goods,
leave your pager number.

12
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:50,000
CLOSED TODAY, JUNE 30TH

13
00:04:50,080 --> 00:04:50,920
Young man,

14
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:54,400
why is the shop closed on June 30th?

15
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:55,840
No idea.

16
00:04:57,120 --> 00:04:58,760
Whatever I ask, you don't know.

17
00:04:58,840 --> 00:05:00,000
Do you work here?

18
00:05:00,080 --> 00:05:02,760
Mister, I only started two days ago.

19
00:05:02,840 --> 00:05:04,200
I haven't even seen the boss.

20
00:05:04,280 --> 00:05:06,160
- You've never seen him?
- No.

21
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:08,320
- Where did he go?
- No idea.

22
00:05:09,640 --> 00:05:11,040
His wife told me

23
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:12,560
to tell anyone who asks where he is
that he's out restocking.

24
00:05:12,640 --> 00:05:15,400
If they ask when he'll be back,
just say I don't know.

25
00:05:15,480 --> 00:05:17,080
So I really don't know.

26
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:33,200
I'm from the Nanshan Branch.
I'm here to ask a few questions.

27
00:05:33,840 --> 00:05:35,960
Hello, Officer. I'm Jessica.
How can I help?

28
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:37,040
JESSICA

29
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:39,720
I'd like to check
the sales record for this dress.

30
00:05:40,480 --> 00:05:42,480
B12200Y.

31
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:43,760
One moment, please.

32
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:47,480
BOWLS

33
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:49,360
This is one of our signature pieces.

34
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:51,920
We've sold 84 pieces
since its spring launch.

35
00:05:52,520 --> 00:05:55,320
- Is there a customer named Sun Zhengyong?
- Let me check.

36
00:06:00,280 --> 00:06:02,960
Yes. Mr. Sun is our VIP client.

37
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:05,840
On May 10th, he bought 11
of the same dress.

38
00:06:05,920 --> 00:06:07,640
Wait, no. Twelve.

39
00:06:07,720 --> 00:06:09,600
We gave him one as a freebie. Have a look.

40
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:12,200
SALES DATE: MAY 10TH, SUN ZHENGYONG

41
00:06:14,440 --> 00:06:19,200
RETURNED 11 DRY-CLEANING VOUCHERS
RECEIVED ONE EXTRA DRESS

42
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:32,520
Where's Captain Feng?
Didn't he want to see me?

43
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:34,160
Officer He, he's in a task force meeting.

44
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:35,120
He told me to wait here for you.

45
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:36,440
This is Jin Manlang's statement
from this afternoon.

46
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:37,520
Take a look.

47
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:39,920
He denied that anyone
had hired him to kill.

48
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,080
He claimed he only went
after Xu Meng and her dad

49
00:06:41,160 --> 00:06:42,160
to collect a debt.

50
00:06:43,960 --> 00:06:46,080
Jin Manlang has grown a pair.
He's trying to retract his confession.

51
00:06:46,160 --> 00:06:49,000
Officer He, there's more.
Jin Manlang said…

52
00:06:49,080 --> 00:06:50,880
What else did he say? Just say it.

53
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:52,680
He said he's going to report you

54
00:06:52,760 --> 00:06:54,040
for forcing a confession.

55
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:59,120
That Wolfie is unbelievable.

56
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:00,400
He's pinning that on me.

57
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:02,360
Bring him in. I want
to question him face-to-face.

58
00:07:02,440 --> 00:07:05,320
JIN MANLANG'S INTERROGATION RECORD

59
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:07,960
JIN MANLANG, SECURITY DEPARTMENT
DEMOLITION DEPARTMENT

60
00:07:08,040 --> 00:07:09,480
LONGWEI GROUP

61
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:10,400
‪2015

62
00:07:11,120 --> 00:07:12,240
It isn't ripe yet.

63
00:07:12,760 --> 00:07:14,080
Seriously.

64
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:16,240
Pick another one for me.

65
00:07:16,320 --> 00:07:17,960
Just that one.

66
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:18,960
RELOCATION BENEFITS ALL
SIGN EARLY, GAIN MORE

67
00:07:21,960 --> 00:07:23,800
- Give it here.
- It's not ripe. Why are you grabbing them?

68
00:07:23,880 --> 00:07:27,000
Come here, I said. Be in your position.

69
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:28,600
Be in your position, okay?

70
00:07:29,520 --> 00:07:30,600
Keep your eyes peeled.

71
00:07:35,520 --> 00:07:36,560
Officer He.

72
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:41,320
What brings you here, sir?

73
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:43,480
Who are you?

74
00:07:45,280 --> 00:07:48,080
It's me. Lang. Lang.

75
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:50,960
JIN MANLANG, SECURITY DEPARTMENT
DEMOLITION DEPARTMENT

76
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:53,640
Look at you all cleaned up.

77
00:07:53,720 --> 00:07:55,600
You're a security manager now, huh?

78
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:58,240
What? Running forced demolitions?

79
00:07:58,760 --> 00:07:59,920
No way.

80
00:08:00,760 --> 00:08:03,200
We keep things civil.

81
00:08:03,280 --> 00:08:05,040
We don't do dirty tricks.

82
00:08:05,120 --> 00:08:07,480
- What brings you here, Officer He?
- I'm here to observe.

83
00:08:08,960 --> 00:08:10,960
Right this way. Please come in.

84
00:08:15,360 --> 00:08:16,560
Welcome.

85
00:08:28,120 --> 00:08:29,040
Everyone,

86
00:08:29,560 --> 00:08:32,120
please let me go over this again.

87
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:35,400
Longwei Group's compensation standards

88
00:08:35,480 --> 00:08:36,480
have always been consistent.

89
00:08:36,559 --> 00:08:37,720
Whether you move in early or late…

90
00:08:37,799 --> 00:08:39,760
Didn't someone say they'd
never come, no matter what?

91
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:44,440
Now, you can take a look
at the notice in your hands.

92
00:08:44,520 --> 00:08:47,920
If you have any questions or doubts,

93
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:50,040
come see me at the Redevelopment Bureau.

94
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:51,040
My name is Qiao Suqing.

95
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:52,000
Feng,

96
00:08:52,520 --> 00:08:55,840
doesn't that woman on stage look familiar?

97
00:08:55,920 --> 00:08:58,840
Wasn't she the mistress
from the fourth floor?

98
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:02,600
Don't believe Du's nonsense.

99
00:09:02,680 --> 00:09:04,800
Qiao is a decent woman.

100
00:09:04,880 --> 00:09:07,040
She's now the finance director
at Longwei Real Estate.

101
00:09:07,720 --> 00:09:10,520
She's in charge of Yuanlongli's
demolition project.

102
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:14,520
Also, if any household needs help moving,

103
00:09:14,600 --> 00:09:16,840
we'll do what we can to assist.

104
00:09:18,280 --> 00:09:20,120
The relocation service is a trap.

105
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:21,200
Don't fall for it.

106
00:09:21,280 --> 00:09:24,040
QIAO SUQING

107
00:09:24,120 --> 00:09:25,320
Even a few hundred yuan would be too much.

108
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:49,400
I can't talk him into it.

109
00:09:49,480 --> 00:09:51,240
Qiao, you're not an outsider here.

110
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:53,160
You tell me. Should he stay or not?

111
00:09:56,560 --> 00:09:57,440
Mr. He,

112
00:09:57,520 --> 00:09:59,640
if even you can't convince him,

113
00:09:59,720 --> 00:10:01,360
I'm not in a position to say anything.

114
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:03,120
Why not?

115
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:05,160
He won't listen to me,

116
00:10:05,240 --> 00:10:06,640
but he might listen to you.

117
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:21,520
You don't have to say it.

118
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:23,720
I can tell from your eyes.

119
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:25,480
You want him to stay.

120
00:10:28,800 --> 00:10:31,280
She's made herself pretty clear.

121
00:10:31,360 --> 00:10:32,720
Say something.

122
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:35,440
Sir, don't put her on the spot.

123
00:10:35,520 --> 00:10:36,920
I'm definitely going back to Beijing.

124
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:38,040
I have classes.

125
00:10:38,120 --> 00:10:40,240
You're the one
putting her in a tough spot.

126
00:10:40,840 --> 00:10:42,760
She wants you to stay.

127
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:44,840
Don't play dumb.

128
00:10:58,000 --> 00:10:59,160
Mr. He,

129
00:11:00,680 --> 00:11:02,360
it's been so long.

130
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:05,360
It's time

131
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:07,040
to let go.

132
00:11:12,120 --> 00:11:14,440
You should let Ran go.

133
00:11:18,080 --> 00:11:20,200
What's wrong with you?
Why won't you ever say what you mean?

134
00:11:20,800 --> 00:11:22,080
- You clearly…
- Sir,

135
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:24,000
just listen to her.

136
00:11:27,360 --> 00:11:29,720
Ran Fangxu, as your mentor,

137
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:32,520
I'm ordering you to stay in Weiyang.

138
00:11:40,040 --> 00:11:42,080
TRAIN TICKET: WEIYANG TO BEIJING

139
00:11:42,160 --> 00:11:43,120
This is a ticket back to Beijing

140
00:11:44,360 --> 00:11:45,320
for tomorrow morning.

141
00:11:54,560 --> 00:11:55,800
Trying to walk back his own confession?

142
00:11:55,880 --> 00:11:56,720
‪1997

143
00:12:00,160 --> 00:12:04,240
SUN BOUGHT THE DRESS
I'LL CHECK THE CCTV IN YUANLONGLI. RAN

144
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:10,600
When one door closes, another opens.

145
00:12:10,680 --> 00:12:12,400
There's always a way through.

146
00:12:15,560 --> 00:12:16,480
Captain Feng.

147
00:12:18,120 --> 00:12:20,200
Officer He, great job.

148
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:23,720
You actually let the suspect
turn the tables on you.

149
00:12:25,320 --> 00:12:26,760
Let him make the noise for now.

150
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:28,480
I'll have them list
everything out soon enough.

151
00:12:28,560 --> 00:12:29,400
No need to wait.

152
00:12:29,480 --> 00:12:31,680
Later, head to HR

153
00:12:31,760 --> 00:12:33,040
and process your transfer back.

154
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:35,560
Also, get Ran over here.

155
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:36,880
We're short-handed here.

156
00:12:39,040 --> 00:12:40,800
Captain Feng, don't.

157
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:43,840
There's still one day left.

158
00:12:48,160 --> 00:12:50,560
You're the leader.
You have to keep your word.

159
00:12:50,640 --> 00:12:52,960
What can you do in one day?

160
00:12:53,040 --> 00:12:54,640
That's barely enough
for you to make a fuss about.

161
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:57,200
Alright. Enough messing around.

162
00:12:57,280 --> 00:12:58,160
Get out of my sight.

163
00:12:58,760 --> 00:13:02,080
Captain Feng, I know
you're not really fed up with me.

164
00:13:02,160 --> 00:13:05,040
You're just annoyed
about that mining case.

165
00:13:05,120 --> 00:13:07,960
By the way, Ran brought in
a pickpocket yesterday.

166
00:13:08,040 --> 00:13:09,200
That guy, Luandongzi.

167
00:13:09,280 --> 00:13:11,760
The task force should follow up on him.

168
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:17,120
- A pickpocket?
- Yeah.

169
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:19,120
Ask if he's stashed a briefcase

170
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:20,600
with "Qingsong Cement" on it.

171
00:13:20,680 --> 00:13:22,160
There's an important document inside.

172
00:13:22,240 --> 00:13:24,400
- That might be useful.
- He Yuanhang.

173
00:13:24,480 --> 00:13:27,760
Wait. What are you talking about?
What briefcase?

174
00:13:27,840 --> 00:13:29,560
He Yuanhang. Get back here!

175
00:13:59,520 --> 00:14:01,120
Sun Zhengyong isn't at the shop.

176
00:14:01,840 --> 00:14:04,680
But I did find something. On June 30th,
he suddenly shut the place down.

177
00:14:04,760 --> 00:14:06,800
That alone puts him on our radar.

178
00:14:06,880 --> 00:14:08,880
Mm. I'm pulling the CCTV from the 30th

179
00:14:08,960 --> 00:14:11,280
to check if he showed up
at Yuanlongli that day.

180
00:14:11,360 --> 00:14:13,280
Leave no stone unturned.

181
00:14:13,800 --> 00:14:14,840
Xinglong.

182
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:16,280
Get me all the footage
from before the 30th.

183
00:14:17,560 --> 00:14:18,720
Got it.

184
00:14:20,760 --> 00:14:21,600
I'll make a call.

185
00:14:29,160 --> 00:14:31,760
- Hello?
- Hello? Qiao?

186
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:34,080
- <i>Officer He.</i>
- Speaking.

187
00:14:34,160 --> 00:14:37,080
- Xiaohe's asleep.
- <i>She's asleep?</i>

188
00:14:37,160 --> 00:14:38,320
How about this?

189
00:14:38,400 --> 00:14:40,720
Could you let her stay
the night at your place?

190
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:42,640
I'll have her grandma
pick her up tomorrow.

191
00:14:42,720 --> 00:14:43,760
<i>Of course.</i>

192
00:14:44,360 --> 00:14:47,520
Officer He, no need
to trouble her grandma.

193
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:50,280
<i>If you're fine with it,</i>
<i>give me the address.</i>

194
00:14:50,360 --> 00:14:51,720
I'll send her there in the morning.

195
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:54,080
I'm totally fine with it. Of course.

196
00:14:54,160 --> 00:14:56,680
<i>Write this down. The address</i>
<i>is 102, Building Unit 2,</i>

197
00:14:56,760 --> 00:14:58,320
Happiness Garden.

198
00:14:58,400 --> 00:15:00,400
Well, sorry to trouble you again.

199
00:15:00,480 --> 00:15:02,000
Not at all.

200
00:15:02,080 --> 00:15:04,720
Alright, I've got the address.

201
00:15:04,800 --> 00:15:07,200
I'll bring Xiaohe over
after breakfast tomorrow.

202
00:15:07,280 --> 00:15:09,280
- Sure. Thank you.
- <i>No problem.</i>

203
00:15:09,360 --> 00:15:10,200
I'll hang up now.

204
00:15:11,680 --> 00:15:13,880
I didn't know much about Qiao before.

205
00:15:14,880 --> 00:15:18,720
But she's really thoughtful

206
00:15:18,800 --> 00:15:20,480
and knows how to carry herself.

207
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:29,240
There are only two people
breathing in this room.

208
00:15:29,320 --> 00:15:30,160
Don't pretend you didn't hear that.

209
00:15:31,800 --> 00:15:34,000
I heard you. Go on.

210
00:15:35,480 --> 00:15:36,760
Yuanlongli

211
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:39,840
is either spreading superstitious nonsense
or making up rumors.

212
00:15:39,920 --> 00:15:42,240
Qiao is a decent person.

213
00:15:43,080 --> 00:15:44,720
How could they smear her as a mistress?

214
00:15:45,360 --> 00:15:47,200
They've gone too far. That's bullying.

215
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:48,560
When I get the time,

216
00:15:48,640 --> 00:15:51,480
I'm going to clean up this toxic mess.

217
00:15:52,640 --> 00:15:53,960
Yeah, someone has to do that.

218
00:16:15,920 --> 00:16:18,040
Are you bringing in a video store here?

219
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:19,760
Didn't you say you wanted everything?

220
00:16:21,040 --> 00:16:23,160
The footage from the past two weeks
is all here.

221
00:16:25,560 --> 00:16:26,680
Take your time.

222
00:16:39,040 --> 00:16:41,960
Xinglong, stop reading papers at night.

223
00:16:42,040 --> 00:16:42,960
You'll ruin your eyes.

224
00:16:43,720 --> 00:16:45,760
- Oh yeah?
- Let me ask you something.

225
00:16:49,280 --> 00:16:51,360
We're looking for this guy.

226
00:16:51,440 --> 00:16:52,320
Rat-faced.

227
00:16:53,120 --> 00:16:55,320
- Do you recognize him?
- No.

228
00:16:57,200 --> 00:16:58,320
That's fine.

229
00:16:58,400 --> 00:17:00,760
You can help us out.
Keep an eye out for him.

230
00:17:00,840 --> 00:17:02,400
Give your eyes a break too.

231
00:17:03,040 --> 00:17:05,040
You call this a break?

232
00:17:05,880 --> 00:17:07,680
Hey. I'm on duty here.

233
00:17:09,319 --> 00:17:11,119
There's a reward if you find him.

234
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:14,480
Then I'll help.

235
00:17:17,160 --> 00:17:18,079
Come.

236
00:17:21,359 --> 00:17:22,599
YUANLONGLI INTERNATIONAL GARDEN

237
00:17:34,520 --> 00:17:36,480
If you spot anyone familiar
or suspicious, call me right away.

238
00:17:37,440 --> 00:17:38,480
Got it.

239
00:17:39,640 --> 00:17:40,840
YUANLONGLI INTERNATIONAL GARDEN

240
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:06,960
YUANLONGLI INTERNATIONAL GARDEN

241
00:18:26,680 --> 00:18:28,680
No. No. My eyes are going blurry.

242
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:31,000
I need to go out and get some air.

243
00:18:31,080 --> 00:18:32,320
My eyes are shot too.

244
00:18:33,040 --> 00:18:34,680
You're young. How could your eyes be shot?

245
00:18:34,760 --> 00:18:36,880
- Keep watching.
- Everything's blurry.

246
00:18:37,640 --> 00:18:38,480
Keep watching.

247
00:18:38,560 --> 00:18:41,480
If it gets that bad,
have Officer Ran buy you some lamb liver.

248
00:18:41,560 --> 00:18:42,680
They're good for the eyes.

249
00:18:48,600 --> 00:18:49,560
He.

250
00:18:50,960 --> 00:18:52,720
What's wrong? Are your eyes blurry too?

251
00:18:52,800 --> 00:18:53,920
It's not that. Look.

252
00:18:58,760 --> 00:19:00,920
Got him? Which day?

253
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:04,120
June 27th. 1:23 p.m.

254
00:19:04,200 --> 00:19:05,960
That lines up. Everything lines up.

255
00:19:06,040 --> 00:19:07,920
On the 27th, Sun Zhengyong

256
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:10,080
scoped out the Qihuang Clinic
on the 17th floor.

257
00:19:10,160 --> 00:19:11,520
He found out it had shut down.

258
00:19:11,600 --> 00:19:12,840
Then he tricked Xu Meng

259
00:19:12,920 --> 00:19:14,480
into bringing her dad there
for treatment on the 30th.

260
00:19:14,560 --> 00:19:15,960
After that, he tipped off the person

261
00:19:16,040 --> 00:19:19,640
who hired Wolfie
and set him up to take the fall.

262
00:19:19,720 --> 00:19:20,960
Meanwhile, he hid in the building

263
00:19:21,040 --> 00:19:22,840
and waited for his chance
to move in on Xu Meng and her dad.

264
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:24,280
It all checks out.

265
00:19:27,960 --> 00:19:31,720
But Xu Meng and her dad
took the elevator to the 18th floor.

266
00:19:31,800 --> 00:19:33,120
How did he know that in advance?

267
00:19:33,200 --> 00:19:34,760
Isn't that obvious?

268
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:37,800
He told Xu Meng the clinic
had moved to the 18th floor.

269
00:19:40,120 --> 00:19:42,600
Then how did he wipe his tracks?

270
00:19:43,360 --> 00:19:45,280
Why are you back
to playing "20 Questions"?

271
00:19:45,360 --> 00:19:47,080
I'll track down his address right now,

272
00:19:47,160 --> 00:19:49,600
drag him in front of you,
and let him explain it himself.

273
00:19:49,680 --> 00:19:50,520
Wait for me.

274
00:19:53,240 --> 00:19:54,640
If I can't find him, I…

275
00:19:54,720 --> 00:19:55,880
Wait. Hold on.

276
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:59,160
Ran. He. It's him.

277
00:19:59,840 --> 00:20:00,760
I… It's him!

278
00:20:01,360 --> 00:20:02,920
That rat-faced guy.

279
00:20:05,800 --> 00:20:07,240
Which day's footage is this?

280
00:20:07,320 --> 00:20:08,480
This isn't footage.

281
00:20:08,560 --> 00:20:10,080
It's live.

282
00:20:13,600 --> 00:20:14,400
Quick.

283
00:20:14,480 --> 00:20:15,640
- Quick.
- Let's go.

284
00:20:18,880 --> 00:20:20,440
- Seventeenth floor. Seventeenth.
- No.

285
00:20:21,200 --> 00:20:23,560
Get off at 16th. Hit both elevators
down to the first floor,

286
00:20:23,640 --> 00:20:25,040
then take the stairs up to the 17th.

287
00:20:25,120 --> 00:20:26,400
We box him in from two sides.

288
00:20:28,360 --> 00:20:31,480
He, you're indeed an expert
in making arrests on-site.

289
00:20:32,800 --> 00:20:35,120
You still have a lot more
to learn. Alright?

290
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:36,920
But I don't get it.

291
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:39,440
What's he doing back
at Yuanlongli right now?

292
00:20:40,520 --> 00:20:42,080
I read this somewhere.

293
00:20:42,160 --> 00:20:45,440
Murderers and lovers
tend to revisit the scene.

294
00:20:45,520 --> 00:20:46,360
I didn't know that.

295
00:20:47,640 --> 00:20:49,000
You still have a lot more to learn.

296
00:21:03,920 --> 00:21:07,360
QIHUANG CLINIC

297
00:21:16,760 --> 00:21:17,800
Sun Zhengyong.

298
00:21:19,840 --> 00:21:20,920
Police.

299
00:21:21,440 --> 00:21:24,400
Stop. Ran, he's heading your way.

300
00:21:41,120 --> 00:21:42,120
Ran Fangxu,

301
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:45,640
taking down suspects
is basic police training.

302
00:21:45,720 --> 00:21:47,480
You need to get past this.

303
00:21:47,560 --> 00:21:48,720
What?

304
00:21:55,880 --> 00:21:57,960
How did you pass
your physical training test?

305
00:21:59,360 --> 00:22:01,680
Shut up. Steady your breathing.
Face him head-on.

306
00:22:06,880 --> 00:22:09,240
Horse stance. Turn into a side lunge.
Block. Trip him.

307
00:22:11,880 --> 00:22:14,360
Shout. Feint a punch.
Knee strike to the abdomen.

308
00:22:26,280 --> 00:22:27,080
Got him.

309
00:22:31,720 --> 00:22:32,760
Still trying to run?

310
00:22:33,960 --> 00:22:36,560
He, thanks for the coaching.

311
00:22:37,840 --> 00:22:38,720
Have some faith.

312
00:22:39,760 --> 00:22:40,600
Are you okay?

313
00:22:43,080 --> 00:22:48,200
FAIR AND JUST, LOYAL AND TRUE

314
00:22:48,280 --> 00:22:49,200
MIRROR

315
00:22:50,200 --> 00:22:51,480
- Over here.
- Move.

316
00:22:59,320 --> 00:23:01,000
- Captain Feng.
- Captain Feng.

317
00:23:03,320 --> 00:23:04,400
Did you crack the case?

318
00:23:05,080 --> 00:23:05,920
We still need to interrogate him.

319
00:23:09,200 --> 00:23:10,120
Upstairs.

320
00:23:22,600 --> 00:23:23,640
Sun Zhengyong,

321
00:23:24,840 --> 00:23:26,160
let's not waste time.

322
00:23:26,240 --> 00:23:27,200
Where's Xu Meng?

323
00:23:27,800 --> 00:23:28,640
Xu Meng?

324
00:23:32,720 --> 00:23:34,640
Do you mean Mengmeng?

325
00:23:34,720 --> 00:23:36,000
Where's Mengmeng?

326
00:23:36,080 --> 00:23:37,760
She took her dad and left.

327
00:23:37,840 --> 00:23:40,040
They bought train tickets for July 1st.

328
00:23:43,400 --> 00:23:44,760
Did you see them leave?

329
00:23:44,840 --> 00:23:45,800
No.

330
00:23:45,880 --> 00:23:48,280
One day, she came to me

331
00:23:48,960 --> 00:23:50,160
and asked to borrow some money.

332
00:23:50,240 --> 00:23:51,280
When?

333
00:23:51,360 --> 00:23:54,000
Around late June.

334
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:58,040
She said someone was threatening her
and wanted her dead.

335
00:23:58,560 --> 00:24:01,160
So she planned to take her dad
and get out of here for good.

336
00:24:01,240 --> 00:24:02,640
But she was worried

337
00:24:02,720 --> 00:24:04,600
the trip would be too much for her dad.

338
00:24:05,200 --> 00:24:09,200
So before leaving, she wanted
to take him to Qihuang Clinic for therapy.

339
00:24:09,800 --> 00:24:11,720
She sounded so pitiful.

340
00:24:12,240 --> 00:24:13,560
I lent her 30,000.

341
00:24:13,640 --> 00:24:15,040
I didn't expect her

342
00:24:15,120 --> 00:24:17,840
to disappear right after taking the money.

343
00:24:20,360 --> 00:24:22,200
Where did you hide them?

344
00:24:22,280 --> 00:24:23,840
I didn't.

345
00:24:26,880 --> 00:24:28,960
Officer, did something happen

346
00:24:29,560 --> 00:24:31,080
to Mengmeng?

347
00:24:32,080 --> 00:24:34,080
You lent her that much money.

348
00:24:34,160 --> 00:24:35,400
What's your relationship?

349
00:24:36,280 --> 00:24:37,440
I like her.

350
00:24:37,520 --> 00:24:39,040
How do you like her?

351
00:24:39,640 --> 00:24:43,040
You know what she does for a living.

352
00:24:43,880 --> 00:24:45,920
I'd book her all the time.

353
00:24:46,000 --> 00:24:48,520
One day, I got drunk.

354
00:24:48,600 --> 00:24:50,360
I told her I wanted to go out with her.

355
00:24:50,880 --> 00:24:54,000
She thought I was talking nonsense
and turned me down.

356
00:24:54,080 --> 00:24:57,080
I was mad. We got into an argument.

357
00:24:57,160 --> 00:24:58,600
And then you forced yourself on her?

358
00:24:58,680 --> 00:25:00,240
No, I didn't. No.

359
00:25:00,320 --> 00:25:03,200
- Did you buy Xu Meng clothes?
- Yeah.

360
00:25:04,400 --> 00:25:05,960
Did you give her a dress from Bowls?

361
00:25:06,040 --> 00:25:08,080
Bowls?

362
00:25:11,080 --> 00:25:12,480
Maybe.

363
00:25:13,360 --> 00:25:15,360
I often go to malls.

364
00:25:15,440 --> 00:25:19,480
When big brands go on sale, I stock up.

365
00:25:19,560 --> 00:25:21,920
First, it makes good gifts for girls.

366
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:24,080
Second, I can copy the design

367
00:25:24,680 --> 00:25:26,240
and get my money back.

368
00:25:28,840 --> 00:25:29,960
Sun Zhengyong,

369
00:25:30,880 --> 00:25:31,920
you can spin tall tales.

370
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:34,920
No matter how well you spin it,
it's still a story.

371
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:36,240
Tell me.

372
00:25:36,320 --> 00:25:39,080
Why did you suddenly
shut your shop on the 30th?

373
00:25:39,160 --> 00:25:43,000
And why were you on the 17th floor
of New York Block on the 27th?

374
00:25:43,840 --> 00:25:45,280
Then this morning,

375
00:25:45,360 --> 00:25:47,320
you went back to No. 1713 again.

376
00:25:47,400 --> 00:25:48,760
And you ran when you saw us.

377
00:25:48,840 --> 00:25:51,360
Try making up a story for all that.

378
00:25:56,160 --> 00:25:57,120
Feeling guilty?

379
00:25:58,200 --> 00:25:59,320
Go on.

380
00:25:59,840 --> 00:26:01,880
I have plenty more evidence
to help you fill in the blanks.

381
00:26:01,960 --> 00:26:02,920
I…

382
00:26:03,680 --> 00:26:04,800
I can't hold it anymore.

383
00:26:04,880 --> 00:26:07,480
Then talk. Where's Xu Meng?

384
00:26:07,560 --> 00:26:08,800
That's not what I meant.

385
00:26:09,640 --> 00:26:11,000
I need the bathroom.

386
00:26:11,720 --> 00:26:13,840
I have prostate issues.

387
00:26:13,920 --> 00:26:15,280
I can't hold it in.

388
00:26:15,360 --> 00:26:19,000
And just now, this officer kicked me.

389
00:26:19,080 --> 00:26:21,320
I really can't take it anymore.

390
00:26:25,520 --> 00:26:27,400
I'm about to burst.

391
00:26:31,520 --> 00:26:34,520
DUTY AND SELF-RESTRAINT
RIGHTEOUSNESS AND PEACE

392
00:26:34,600 --> 00:26:35,440
Look who it is.

393
00:26:35,520 --> 00:26:37,360
The famous Officer He.

394
00:26:38,080 --> 00:26:39,360
Still with the Criminal Department?

395
00:26:39,440 --> 00:26:40,880
Not coming back?

396
00:26:40,960 --> 00:26:42,880
Of course. This is
where the big cases are.

397
00:26:42,960 --> 00:26:46,600
Unlike someone who couldn't
even handle public order.

398
00:26:46,680 --> 00:26:47,800
Keep bragging. Go on.

399
00:26:47,880 --> 00:26:49,160
Big cases? How big?

400
00:26:49,240 --> 00:26:50,480
Bigger than a task force case?

401
00:26:50,560 --> 00:26:52,600
Do you have to give proper case briefings?

402
00:26:52,680 --> 00:26:54,520
You're just someone
stringing up police tape,

403
00:26:54,600 --> 00:26:55,840
and now you're talking
task force briefings?

404
00:26:55,920 --> 00:26:57,400
You sure have a knack
for blowing your own trumpet.

405
00:26:57,480 --> 00:26:58,480
And you're any better?

406
00:26:58,560 --> 00:27:00,680
Still chasing that prank case, aren't you?

407
00:27:00,760 --> 00:27:02,480
Come on. Let me see.
What big suspect did you catch?

408
00:27:04,400 --> 00:27:05,520
Officer Qu.

409
00:27:06,280 --> 00:27:08,640
He Yuanhang, are you trying to amuse me?

410
00:27:09,480 --> 00:27:10,920
A criminal investigator like you

411
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:12,720
is actually busting
a street vendor selling fakes?

412
00:27:14,880 --> 00:27:16,600
Officer Qu, do you know this guy?

413
00:27:17,200 --> 00:27:18,440
He's Mr. Sun.

414
00:27:18,520 --> 00:27:21,080
He shows up at the station twice a week.

415
00:27:21,160 --> 00:27:22,240
Busier than Officer He.

416
00:27:23,280 --> 00:27:24,120
A week?

417
00:27:24,200 --> 00:27:26,440
- When was he brought in?
- Last week.

418
00:27:27,080 --> 00:27:28,360
June 29th.

419
00:27:28,440 --> 00:27:30,640
He was selling counterfeit goods
and got into a fight.

420
00:27:30,720 --> 00:27:32,800
He was brought in and held for five days.

421
00:27:39,320 --> 00:27:42,680
You suspect he has something to do
with that prank case?

422
00:27:45,320 --> 00:27:47,800
I can vouch for him. It wasn't him.

423
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:49,320
He didn't have the time.

424
00:27:58,600 --> 00:28:02,960
Officer, if I don't go now,
I'm going to piss myself.

425
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:09,400
DUTY AND SELF-RESTRAINT
RIGHTEOUSNESS AND PEACE

426
00:28:16,520 --> 00:28:17,680
Officer,

427
00:28:18,320 --> 00:28:20,160
about the first question from earlier,

428
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:21,920
you already know the answer.

429
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:25,280
Now I'll answer the second and third.

430
00:28:25,360 --> 00:28:29,040
I ran when I saw you because I panicked.

431
00:28:29,120 --> 00:28:32,000
I thought you were after
my counterfeit business.

432
00:28:32,080 --> 00:28:34,480
As for the 17th floor at New York Block,

433
00:28:34,560 --> 00:28:37,800
there's a tailor there I work with.

434
00:28:37,880 --> 00:28:40,600
Last week, I took the fabric
to make samples.

435
00:28:41,200 --> 00:28:43,880
This morning, I went to collect
the finished goods.

436
00:28:43,960 --> 00:28:45,960
But when I got to the 17th,

437
00:28:46,040 --> 00:28:49,240
I didn't know why, something just hit me.

438
00:28:49,320 --> 00:28:50,520
I suddenly thought of Mengmeng.

439
00:28:51,360 --> 00:28:53,760
So I figured I'd check out Qihuang Clinic.

440
00:28:53,840 --> 00:28:57,720
I didn't know it had shut down.

441
00:28:57,800 --> 00:29:00,120
Mengmeng played me.

442
00:29:00,200 --> 00:29:02,320
That's enough. You don't need to go on.

443
00:29:02,960 --> 00:29:07,040
You really shouldn't
get too close to unlucky people.

444
00:29:07,120 --> 00:29:09,360
Bad luck spreads like a disease.

445
00:29:09,440 --> 00:29:11,200
Once it sticks, it rubs off.

446
00:29:13,360 --> 00:29:17,000
Officer, did Mengmeng go missing?

447
00:29:18,240 --> 00:29:20,320
That might be the best outcome

448
00:29:20,840 --> 00:29:22,480
for the people around her.

449
00:29:22,560 --> 00:29:25,000
Enough said. Spare me the act.

450
00:29:25,080 --> 00:29:26,160
You're no saint yourself.

451
00:29:26,240 --> 00:29:27,440
You're too rotten
for bad luck to touch you.

452
00:29:30,120 --> 00:29:31,240
Can you take these off now?

453
00:29:53,960 --> 00:29:55,840
- Mr. Song.
- What is it?

454
00:29:55,920 --> 00:29:57,320
Cripple Du's men were tailing me.

455
00:29:57,400 --> 00:29:58,920
Just as I dug the body up,

456
00:29:59,000 --> 00:30:01,520
they snatched it and took my car.

457
00:30:02,880 --> 00:30:05,440
- What did you just say?
- I'm telling the truth.

458
00:30:05,520 --> 00:30:07,680
Look at this. My head
has been thrashed badly.

459
00:30:30,560 --> 00:30:31,400
Who sent this over?

460
00:30:42,920 --> 00:30:44,400
- Who?
- <i>Song Qingsong,</i>

461
00:30:45,360 --> 00:30:46,760
<i>did you see the photo?</i>

462
00:30:48,240 --> 00:30:50,920
Director Li, what photo? I have no idea.

463
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:52,800
<i>Stop pretending.</i>

464
00:30:52,880 --> 00:30:55,280
<i>That photo was left right at my doorstep.</i>

465
00:30:56,400 --> 00:30:57,280
<i>Song Qingsong,</i>

466
00:30:57,800 --> 00:30:59,440
<i>I don't care if you make dirty money.</i>

467
00:31:00,280 --> 00:31:01,960
<i>But you actually killed someone.</i>

468
00:31:03,560 --> 00:31:05,440
Director Li, hear me out.

469
00:31:05,520 --> 00:31:07,480
<i>Someone has died! Hear you out for what?</i>

470
00:31:08,280 --> 00:31:10,840
<i>Listen carefully. Go on the run.</i>

471
00:31:10,920 --> 00:31:12,600
- <i>Right now.</i>
- Alright. Drop the act.

472
00:31:12,680 --> 00:31:13,720
<i>What did you say?</i>

473
00:31:14,400 --> 00:31:16,360
Did you get Cripple Du to take my car

474
00:31:17,200 --> 00:31:18,920
and have someone seal the bid document?

475
00:31:19,000 --> 00:31:20,360
<i>Song Qingsong.</i>

476
00:31:20,880 --> 00:31:21,640
- <i>I…</i>
- Li.

477
00:31:21,720 --> 00:31:23,400
Listen up.

478
00:31:23,480 --> 00:31:25,760
I didn't burn the bid you sold me.

479
00:31:25,840 --> 00:31:27,040
So here are your options.

480
00:31:27,120 --> 00:31:31,520
One, I keep Dongshan Mine
and you tell Cripple Du to get lost.

481
00:31:32,160 --> 00:31:33,960
Second, you return the eight million.

482
00:31:34,040 --> 00:31:35,960
Otherwise, we both go down together.

483
00:31:36,040 --> 00:31:37,640
We all go down together!

484
00:31:37,720 --> 00:31:39,280
<i>Song Qingsong,</i>

485
00:31:39,360 --> 00:31:41,960
<i>between bribery and murder,</i>
<i>which one carries the heavier sentence?</i>

486
00:31:42,040 --> 00:31:43,480
<i>We're not going down together.</i>

487
00:31:43,560 --> 00:31:45,000
I'm not scared!

488
00:31:45,080 --> 00:31:46,280
I have money.

489
00:31:46,360 --> 00:31:48,200
I could kill more and still
find someone to take the fall.

490
00:31:48,280 --> 00:31:50,640
What can you do to me? What can you do?

491
00:31:57,600 --> 00:32:00,360
<i>I'm not scared! I have money.</i>

492
00:32:00,440 --> 00:32:02,360
<i>I could kill more and still</i>
<i>find someone to take the fall.</i>

493
00:32:02,440 --> 00:32:05,600
<i>What can you do to me? What can you do?</i>

494
00:32:07,560 --> 00:32:10,160
<i>I'm not scared! I have money.</i>

495
00:32:10,240 --> 00:32:11,920
<i>I could kill more and still</i>
<i>find someone to take the fall.</i>

496
00:32:12,000 --> 00:32:14,320
<i>What can you do to me? What can you do?</i>

497
00:32:15,600 --> 00:32:17,000
<i>Song Qingsong,</i>

498
00:32:17,520 --> 00:32:20,360
<i>you're not just ignorant of the law,</i>
<i>you are stupid.</i>

499
00:32:20,440 --> 00:32:21,280
Son of a bitch.

500
00:32:21,360 --> 00:32:23,040
You are despicable.

501
00:32:23,560 --> 00:32:25,760
<i>Now I'll give you two options.</i>

502
00:32:25,840 --> 00:32:27,080
<i>One, I burn the photo,</i>

503
00:32:27,760 --> 00:32:28,720
<i>you go out and lie low for a while.</i>

504
00:32:29,320 --> 00:32:33,000
<i>Two, I hand the photo and the recording</i>
<i>over to the police.</i>

505
00:32:33,520 --> 00:32:36,880
<i>Keep both your money and your life</i>
<i>or lose everything. Your call.</i>

506
00:32:39,160 --> 00:32:41,360
Mr… Mr. Song. Mr. Song. Mr. Song.

507
00:32:41,440 --> 00:32:44,160
I was wrong. Mr. Song. Forgive me.

508
00:32:44,680 --> 00:32:47,000
- It's my fault.
- All of you

509
00:32:47,800 --> 00:32:49,400
are trying to screw me over.

510
00:32:49,480 --> 00:32:51,480
Mr. Song. Forgive me.

511
00:33:23,480 --> 00:33:25,280
WEIYANG CITY DONGSHAN MINE BID DOCUMENT

512
00:33:36,160 --> 00:33:38,000
Book me two tickets to Los Angeles.

513
00:33:38,880 --> 00:33:40,040
As soon as possible.

514
00:33:40,680 --> 00:33:42,880
<i>Got it, Mr. Song. Who's going with you?</i>

515
00:33:51,320 --> 00:33:54,120
QINGSONG CEMENT FACTORY, WEIYANG CITY

516
00:33:56,600 --> 00:33:59,440
QINGSONG CEMENT FACTORY

517
00:34:10,080 --> 00:34:12,239
Mr. Song. Cripple Du's men are here.

518
00:34:13,920 --> 00:34:14,760
Go.

519
00:34:17,400 --> 00:34:18,960
‪-Stop!
‪-Don't run!

520
00:34:19,040 --> 00:34:20,679
‪-Stay there!
‪-Don't run!

521
00:34:27,840 --> 00:34:29,199
Qingsong. Take the back door.

522
00:34:29,280 --> 00:34:30,239
We leave together.

523
00:34:30,320 --> 00:34:32,360
Too late. We don't have time. Qingsong.

524
00:34:32,440 --> 00:34:34,280
Don't worry, Qingsong.
The police won't trace it here.

525
00:34:34,360 --> 00:34:37,040
Even if they do,
I'll take the fall. Go now.

526
00:34:38,239 --> 00:34:40,120
As long as you, my sister,
and your child are safe,

527
00:34:40,199 --> 00:34:41,679
even if I take a bullet for it,

528
00:34:41,760 --> 00:34:43,040
it'll be worth it.

529
00:34:43,120 --> 00:34:46,320
Shanlong, after I'm gone,
you're the factory director.

530
00:34:46,920 --> 00:34:48,239
Take care of everything for me.

531
00:34:48,840 --> 00:34:51,400
- Qingsong, go. Qingsong, go.
- I'll be back.

532
00:34:51,480 --> 00:34:53,000
- I'll be back.
- Go, Qingsong.

533
00:34:53,080 --> 00:34:54,920
Qingsong, go.

534
00:34:58,520 --> 00:34:59,640
‪Fucking hell!

535
00:35:07,200 --> 00:35:09,720
Stop! Stop! Stop!

536
00:35:23,640 --> 00:35:25,720
I paid you to put on a show.

537
00:35:26,240 --> 00:35:28,120
You're actually beating me?

538
00:35:28,200 --> 00:35:31,520
For real? How dare you!

539
00:35:31,600 --> 00:35:32,560
Fuck.

540
00:35:32,640 --> 00:35:34,480
Motherfuckers.

541
00:35:36,960 --> 00:35:38,400
Can you be professional?

542
00:36:23,480 --> 00:36:25,040
You got lucky this time.

543
00:36:25,800 --> 00:36:28,040
It's not going to happen a third time.

544
00:36:48,080 --> 00:36:53,240
FAIR AND JUST, LOYAL AND TRUE

545
00:36:53,320 --> 00:36:55,880
INTERROGATION ROOM

546
00:37:02,600 --> 00:37:04,400
I was trying to prove myself.

547
00:37:04,480 --> 00:37:05,680
But then,

548
00:37:06,360 --> 00:37:08,160
I proved I was a fool.

549
00:37:11,040 --> 00:37:13,560
Now our only lead is Song Qingsong.

550
00:37:15,800 --> 00:37:18,800
- Let's go.
- Hurry up. Quit dragging your feet.

551
00:37:19,480 --> 00:37:21,440
Officer, my leg hurts.

552
00:37:21,520 --> 00:37:22,600
Wu Shanlong?

553
00:37:23,520 --> 00:37:26,400
FAIR AND JUST

554
00:37:27,560 --> 00:37:28,840
Good day, officers.

555
00:37:29,600 --> 00:37:31,600
- What's he in for?
- It's a misunderstanding.

556
00:37:32,120 --> 00:37:34,000
- Misunderstanding.
- Did they ask you?

557
00:37:35,280 --> 00:37:38,400
It's about Dongshan Mine.
We'll need to question him further.

558
00:37:38,480 --> 00:37:39,600
Have you arrested Song Qingsong?

559
00:37:39,680 --> 00:37:40,920
Reporting, sir.

560
00:37:41,680 --> 00:37:42,640
From now on,

561
00:37:42,720 --> 00:37:44,920
there'll be no more
Song Qingsong in Weiyang.

562
00:37:45,000 --> 00:37:46,200
End of report.

563
00:37:48,080 --> 00:37:49,080
Move.

564
00:37:59,960 --> 00:38:04,000
RUICHUAN RESTAURANT

565
00:38:05,480 --> 00:38:07,040
One faked you out,

566
00:38:07,560 --> 00:38:08,800
the other got away.

567
00:38:09,680 --> 00:38:13,000
These two are cunning.

568
00:38:14,280 --> 00:38:15,320
Stop reading.

569
00:38:15,920 --> 00:38:16,760
He got away.

570
00:38:16,840 --> 00:38:18,400
What's the point of staring
at the notebook?

571
00:38:18,480 --> 00:38:19,560
Eat the noodles. Come on.

572
00:38:24,440 --> 00:38:25,800
Stop reading.

573
00:38:25,880 --> 00:38:27,080
Listen.

574
00:38:27,160 --> 00:38:29,040
We're putting this case on hold for now.

575
00:38:29,120 --> 00:38:31,240
I've talked to Captain Feng.

576
00:38:31,320 --> 00:38:32,360
After this meal,

577
00:38:32,440 --> 00:38:34,000
you report to the Task Force.

578
00:38:34,080 --> 00:38:35,080
As for me,

579
00:38:35,840 --> 00:38:37,200
I'm going back to the station.

580
00:38:54,240 --> 00:38:55,160
He,

581
00:38:56,520 --> 00:38:57,400
are you backing out?

582
00:38:59,920 --> 00:39:01,600
How can you call this backing out?

583
00:39:01,680 --> 00:39:05,080
This is getting back to where we belong
and doing our part.

584
00:39:05,160 --> 00:39:06,480
Getting back is backing out.

585
00:39:08,400 --> 00:39:10,880
We've taken a beating over a missing case
that hasn't even been filed.

586
00:39:10,960 --> 00:39:13,520
And now you say don't back out,
tell me how we move forward.

587
00:39:14,560 --> 00:39:16,640
Besides, we had an agreement
with Captain Feng.

588
00:39:16,720 --> 00:39:19,720
Today's the third day.
We have to keep our word.

589
00:39:20,640 --> 00:39:21,560
We still have tonight.

590
00:39:22,560 --> 00:39:25,080
Ran Fangxu, are you stupid or what?

591
00:39:26,040 --> 00:39:27,960
The task force has brought in Wu Shanlong.

592
00:39:28,040 --> 00:39:30,040
If you don't report in now,
forget the credit,

593
00:39:30,120 --> 00:39:31,640
you won't even get a shred of it.

594
00:39:31,720 --> 00:39:33,920
I didn't become a cop for credit.

595
00:39:34,000 --> 00:39:36,480
I owe Xu Meng and her dad the truth.

596
00:39:51,240 --> 00:39:54,040
He, after everything we've done,

597
00:39:54,800 --> 00:39:57,440
if we pull out now,
it'll all be for nothing.

598
00:39:57,960 --> 00:39:59,200
Let me tell you this.

599
00:40:00,640 --> 00:40:03,880
I've lived long enough to learn one thing.

600
00:40:04,480 --> 00:40:05,920
Don't get too hung up on things.

601
00:40:06,000 --> 00:40:07,840
Let go when you can.

602
00:40:07,920 --> 00:40:10,480
Or else, you'll drive yourself crazy.

603
00:40:27,960 --> 00:40:30,120
Looks like my first case

604
00:40:31,360 --> 00:40:32,720
is going to end in failure.

605
00:40:40,440 --> 00:40:42,680
Ever since I entered PPSUC,

606
00:40:43,440 --> 00:40:45,680
I've been studying all kinds
of missing person cases.

607
00:40:47,840 --> 00:40:49,200
I told myself that once
I became a police officer

608
00:40:50,000 --> 00:40:51,640
and took on a case,

609
00:40:51,720 --> 00:40:54,120
I'd find the missing person at all costs

610
00:40:55,280 --> 00:40:56,840
and leave no regrets.

611
00:41:01,080 --> 00:41:03,840
I thought I knew my stuff.

612
00:41:04,440 --> 00:41:06,080
But when it comes to real fieldwork,

613
00:41:08,560 --> 00:41:09,520
I'm nothing.

614
00:41:22,000 --> 00:41:23,000
That's funny.

615
00:41:24,080 --> 00:41:25,120
You know what?

616
00:41:26,440 --> 00:41:28,520
My first case
was a missing persons case too.

617
00:41:28,600 --> 00:41:31,160
It was an old man with dementia.

618
00:41:32,120 --> 00:41:33,680
I ran around for days,

619
00:41:33,760 --> 00:41:35,480
nearly wore my shoes out.

620
00:41:39,600 --> 00:41:40,880
So you failed too?

621
00:41:44,800 --> 00:41:46,000
I ran out of leads

622
00:41:46,800 --> 00:41:47,800
and had to try something stupid.

623
00:42:01,520 --> 00:42:02,880
Enough with the suspense.

624
00:42:03,960 --> 00:42:05,400
No. It's not that.

625
00:42:06,840 --> 00:42:07,720
Here's what I did.

626
00:42:08,560 --> 00:42:11,120
I pretended to be the old man

627
00:42:11,200 --> 00:42:13,920
and followed his way of thinking.

628
00:42:14,000 --> 00:42:14,880
I wandered around aimlessly.

629
00:42:14,960 --> 00:42:17,360
When I was hungry,
I grabbed whatever I could find.

630
00:42:17,440 --> 00:42:18,760
When I needed to pee,

631
00:42:18,840 --> 00:42:20,000
I just went wherever.

632
00:42:21,480 --> 00:42:22,360
And in the end,

633
00:42:22,440 --> 00:42:24,520
I actually found him.

634
00:42:28,360 --> 00:42:29,800
He.

635
00:42:29,880 --> 00:42:31,800
That's basically immersive roleplay.

636
00:42:34,280 --> 00:42:36,080
Yeah. Right.

637
00:42:37,680 --> 00:42:38,600
I came up with this myself

638
00:42:39,720 --> 00:42:41,360
22 years before you.

639
00:42:46,320 --> 00:42:49,240
How about we…

640
00:42:55,080 --> 00:42:56,360
No way.

641
00:42:59,400 --> 00:43:00,760
Listen.

642
00:43:00,840 --> 00:43:02,120
If you want to do that, go ahead.

643
00:43:02,200 --> 00:43:04,320
Anyone who goes with you
is out of their mind.

644
00:43:09,960 --> 00:43:10,960
NOTEBOOK

645
00:43:47,880 --> 00:43:49,760
Can you not breathe all over me?

646
00:43:49,840 --> 00:43:50,880
What?

647
00:43:51,400 --> 00:43:54,320
That old man in the footage
kept his head down like this.

648
00:43:55,400 --> 00:43:57,240
You smell like garlic.

649
00:43:57,320 --> 00:43:59,320
Focus on your job.

650
00:44:17,960 --> 00:44:20,360
Focus on your job. Lean back.

651
00:44:20,440 --> 00:44:21,800
You're getting back at me.

652
00:44:38,360 --> 00:44:40,200
Why are your legs shaking?

653
00:44:40,280 --> 00:44:42,440
You should lose some weight.

654
00:44:42,520 --> 00:44:43,720
If you can't handle it, I'll switch.

655
00:44:43,800 --> 00:44:45,200
Don't move.

656
00:44:45,280 --> 00:44:47,440
If we can't get it right this time,
we run it again.

657
00:44:52,440 --> 00:44:54,320
- I'm taking my jacket off.
- Steady.

658
00:45:04,720 --> 00:45:05,840
PRIVATE ROOM 1

659
00:45:06,880 --> 00:45:07,880
Hey.

660
00:45:07,960 --> 00:45:10,160
Have you picked up anything so far?

661
00:45:10,880 --> 00:45:11,800
No.

662
00:45:12,320 --> 00:45:14,840
Have you felt anything back there?

663
00:45:15,600 --> 00:45:16,600
I have.

664
00:45:17,360 --> 00:45:18,240
What is it?

665
00:45:18,320 --> 00:45:20,400
Xu Meng has better stamina than you.

666
00:45:28,960 --> 00:45:30,040
I may not have gone to the Police Academy,

667
00:45:30,760 --> 00:45:32,960
but I've been a cop for 22 years.

668
00:45:33,040 --> 00:45:35,160
I have my own ways of working things out.

669
00:45:35,760 --> 00:45:36,680
Let's hear it.

670
00:45:37,520 --> 00:45:39,920
Everything is always changing.
We only have so much energy.

671
00:45:40,000 --> 00:45:41,400
Focus on the big picture.
Don't dwell on the small stuff.

672
00:45:41,480 --> 00:45:43,040
Dress well, eat well.

673
00:45:43,640 --> 00:45:44,520
I understand the first three.

674
00:45:45,200 --> 00:45:46,840
What's that last one supposed to mean?

675
00:45:47,360 --> 00:45:50,240
Simple. What can't you live without?

676
00:45:50,320 --> 00:45:51,600
Eat, drink, sleep, and poop.

677
00:45:51,680 --> 00:45:53,160
It's in those everyday things

678
00:45:53,240 --> 00:45:54,680
that people slip up and leave traces.

679
00:45:54,760 --> 00:45:56,640
Take this cola.

680
00:45:56,720 --> 00:45:58,960
You pop it open, and it sprays everywhere.
You shake it off, right?

681
00:45:59,040 --> 00:46:02,880
And when you do, you leave a trail. Right?

682
00:46:05,080 --> 00:46:06,160
What are you looking at?

683
00:46:06,240 --> 00:46:08,880
He. Look. What's that?

684
00:46:11,840 --> 00:46:14,480
Isn't that where I shook off
the cola last time?

685
00:46:14,560 --> 00:46:15,680
No.

686
00:46:15,760 --> 00:46:17,480
Look higher. Up there.

687
00:46:25,600 --> 00:46:26,760
In the CCTV,

688
00:46:26,840 --> 00:46:29,000
Xu Meng's dad was holding a cigarette.

689
00:46:29,080 --> 00:46:30,360
He has a lung condition.

690
00:46:30,440 --> 00:46:31,760
<i>Why would he be smoking?</i>

691
00:47:14,760 --> 00:47:16,640
Easy. Stay calm.
